<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{ya}}}} is used to join nouns in a non-exhaustive list. Its use implies that the nouns
listed are some examples taken from a larger list. In this usage @HI{{@EM{{ya}}}} is
often combined with <a href="grammar-particle-nado.html">@HI{{nado}}</a>. Compare @HI{{@EM{{ya}}}} 
with <a href="grammar-particle-to.html">@HI{{to}}</a>, which can be used to provide an exhaustive listing
of nouns.

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{ya}}}} cannot be used to combine predicates, only nouns or noun phrases.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{ya}}}} inexhaustively lists items that are related to a specific time and place, whereas
<a href="grammar-particle-toka.html">@HI{{toka}}</a> inexhaustively lists items in a more general fashion.
</p>

